text: Mark McGowan (born 13 July 1967) is a Western Australian former politician who served as the 30th Premier of Western Australia from 17 March 2017 until 8 June 2023. He is from the Labor Party. He was replaced by Roger Cook. ==References== Category:1967 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Perth, Western Australia Category:Premiers of Western Australia Category:Australian Labor Party politicians Category:Politicians from New South Wales
